                    "description": "As a lecturer for the bachelor's degree Future Planet Studies at the University of Amsterdam, I was responsible for among other things tutoring, grading and lecturing about topics related to sustainability and global environmental issues to first-third year bachelor students. Furthermore, I was involved in development of course material and assignments for several courses, including Water Quality, academic writing and systems thinking (Toekomstige Uitdagingen, Innovatieve Oplossingen) and Natuurrampen & toekomstige bedreigingen (Natural Disasters and Future Hazards), for which I also give a 3-hour lecture on wildfires each year. Courses I was involved in were: \n\n\n- Analyse IPCC Rapport (Analysis IPCC Report)\n- Complex problems: the food issue\n- Digital earth\n- Energietransities (Energy transitions)\n- Natuurrampen & toekomstige bedreigingen (Natural disasters & Future hazards)\n- Quality of life research\n- Soil & plant interactions\n- Toekomstperspectief voor de aarde (Future perspective of the Earth)\n- Toekomstige uitdagingen, innovatieve oplossingen (Future Challenges, Innovative Solutions)\n- Virtual globe\n- Water quality\n- World food and ecosystems",
